        <p><lb n="1"/><g type="mangala"/><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> valkhāḥ paramabhaṭṭāraka-pādānuddhyāto mahārāja-bhuluṇḍas samājñāpayati sarvvā<!-- 
L1 RT: transcribes mangala as om 
--><lb break="no" n="2"/>
n evāsmat-santakān āyuktakān
</p>
        <p>vijñā<choice>
            <sic>na</sic>
            <corr>ta</corr>
          </choice>m astu vaḥ samanujānīmo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>sya valkhā<supplied reason="omitted">yā</supplied>m eva
<lb n="3"/>bhojikā-bhaṭṭa-bandhulayā pratiṣṭhāpitaka-bappapiśācadevasya tat-preṣitaka-
<lb n="4"/>jaya-vijñāpyāt tasya Eva santakaṁ kodravatallakan nāma-grāmaṁ bali-caru-satra-
<lb n="5"/>dhūpa-gan<unclear>dh</unclear>a-mālya-pu<choice>
            <sic>ppa</sic>
            <corr>ṣpo</corr>
          </choice>payojyaṁ devāgrāhāra-krameṇa śāśvatam ācandrā<sic>rk</sic>a-tāra<lb break="no" n="6"/>
kā-kālīnaṁ bhogāyaivam idānīm asyāsmābhiḥ kr̥tānujñasyocitayā devāgrā<lb break="no" n="7"/>
hāra-bhuktyā tad-devakulāśritāḥ pāśupatācāryya-bhagavac-chi<choice>
            <sic>nta</sic>
            <corr>ṣṭā</corr>
          </choice>dayo deva-karmmi<lb break="no" n="8"/>
ṇaś ca bhuñjānās samāvāsayānāś ca sarvvair evāsmat-pa<supplied reason="omitted">kṣa</supplied>-tat-kulyādibhiḥ samanumanta<lb break="no" n="9"/>
vyam i<choice>
            <sic>d</sic>
            <corr>t</corr>
          </choice>i</p>
